Package com.samskivert.depot

The bulk of the Depot public API.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    CacheAdapter
    Implementations of this interface are responsible for all the caching needs of Depot.
    CacheAdapter.CachedValue<T>
    The encapsulated result of a cache lookup.
    CacheInvalidator
    Implementors of this interface performs perform cache invalidation for calls to DepotRepository.updatePartial(com.samskivert.depot.Key<T>, com.samskivert.depot.expression.ColumnExp<?>, java.lang.Object, java.lang.Object...) and DepotRepository.deleteAll(java.lang.Class<T>, com.samskivert.depot.clause.WhereClause).
    CacheKey
    This interface uniquely identifies a single persistent entry for caching purposes.
    PersistenceContext.CacheListener<T>
    A cache listener is notified when cache entries change.
    PersistenceContext.CacheTraverser<T extends Serializable>
    The callback for PersistenceContext.cacheTraverse(java.lang.Class<? extends com.samskivert.depot.PersistentRecord>, com.samskivert.depot.PersistenceContext.CacheTraverser<T>); this is called for each entry in a given cache.
    SQLFragment
    Represents a fragment of an SQL statement, generally a clause (WHERE, FROM, ...) or an expression (1+1, 'foo', "columnName", ...).
    ValidatingCacheInvalidator
    An augmented cache invalidator interface for invalidators that can ensure that they are operating on the proper persistent record class.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    CacheInvalidator.TraverseWithFilter<T extends Serializable>  
    CountRecord
    Handy record for computing the count of something.
    DataMigration
    Encapsulates a migration of data between entities that should be run only once and using the same safeguards applied to entity migrations.
    DateFuncs
    Provides static methods for date-related function construction.
    DepotRepository
    Provides a base for classes that provide access to persistent objects.
    EHCacheAdapter
    An implementation of CacheAdapter for ehcache where each CacheAdapter.CacheCategory results in one Ehcache.
    EHCacheAdapter.EHCacheConfig  
    EHCacheAdapter.EHCachePerformance  
    Exps
    Provides static methods for expression construction.
    Funcs
    Provides static methods for function construction.
    Key<T extends PersistentRecord>
    A special form of WhereClause that uniquely specifies a single database row and thus also a single persistent object.
    Key.Expression
    Handles the matching of the key columns to its bound values.
    KeySet<T extends PersistentRecord>
    Contains a set of primary keys that match a set of persistent records.
    Log
    Contains a reference to the log object used by this package.
    MathFuncs
    Provides static methods for math-related function construction.
    Ops
    Provides static methods for operator construction that don't fit nicely into the fluent style.
    PersistenceContext
    Defines a scope in which global annotations are shared.
    PersistenceContext.CacheEvictionFilter<T extends Serializable>
    A simple implementation of PersistenceContext.CacheTraverser that selectively deletes entries in a cache depending on the return value of PersistenceContext.CacheEvictionFilter.testForEviction(java.io.Serializable, T).
    PersistentRecord
    The base class for all persistent records used in Depot.
    Query<T extends PersistentRecord>
    The root of a fluent mechanism for constructing queries.
    SchemaMigration
    Encapsulates the migration of a persistent record's database schema.
    SchemaMigration.Add
    A convenient migration for adding a new column that requires a default value to be specified during the addition.
    SchemaMigration.Drop
    A convenient migration for dropping a column from an entity.
    SchemaMigration.DropIndex
    A convenient migration for dropping a column from an entity.
    SchemaMigration.Rename
    A convenient migration for renaming a column in an entity.
    SchemaMigration.Retype
    A convenient migration for changing the type of an existing field.
    Stats
    Manages Depot performance statistics.
    Stats.Snapshot
    An immutable class used to report statistics on repository activity.
    StringFuncs
    Provides static methods for string-related function construction.
    Transformer<F,T>
    Transforms a persistent record field into a format that can be read and written by the underlying database.
    Transformers
    Contains various generally useful Transformer implementations.
    Transformers.ByteEnumSet<E extends Enum<E> & com.samskivert.util.ByteEnum>
    Transform a Set of ByteEnums into an Integer.
    Transformers.EnumIterable<E extends Enum<E>>
    A Transformer for anything that is an Iterable<Enum>.
    Transformers.IntegerIterable
    Can transform a List/Set/Collection/Iterable to an int[] for storage in the db.
    Transformers.StringArray
    Combines the contents of a String[] column into a single String, terminating each String element with a newline.
    Transformers.StringIterable
    Combines the contents of a List/Set/Collection/Iterable<String> column into a single String, terminating each String element with a newline.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    CacheAdapter.CacheCategory  
    DepotRepository.CacheStrategy  
    PersistenceContext.CanMigrate
    Used by PersistenceContext.PersistenceContext(CanMigrate).
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    DatabaseException
    Represents a failure reported by the underlying database.
    DuplicateKeyException
    Thrown when an insert or update results in a duplicate key on a column that has a uniqueness constraint.
